Delivery options

Your are about to finalize your order to certify Portrait of a Lady by Tetu, 2020 ( 1 / 15 ). The certificate is valid for a duration of 10 years. You can order to e-mail and print the certificate yourself, or you can order to mail and receive a printed document by post.

Order by mail

We activate the digital certificate immediately, we print the documents and you will receive the physical certificates by post within a few days.

(available SOON!)

Do it yourself (DIY) instructions

If you order to e-mail, you will receive two PDF documents at your email address tuteu@uncopied.art. The first PDF document contains the 15 certificates. The second PDF document contains the 15 tally sticks (example below),

  • Print the certificate document in 4 copies
  • Print the tally stick document on quality 100-gram paper
  • Sign manually each part of the tally stick, just below the title
  • Cut along the blue lines with good scissors
  • Glue the central part of the tally stick to the back of the artwork
  • Glue each other part of the tally stick to one certificate copy
  • The issuer copy should be retained by the artist for the record
  • The owner copy is given to the owner when the artwork is sold
  • Send the two certificate copies by post to the PO Box address
Printing should be made on 100-gram high quality paper (recommended brand). Cutting should be done manually with good quality scissors. Gluing should be done with strong, permanent and transparent glue that will not affect the artwork's long term preservation (recommended brand). We will activate the digital certificate as soon as we have received the physical copies from you by post.
